Figure 3.1: Spectral contribution to the observed interference colour as a function of birefringence. Assumes a uniform light source (even spectral distribution). The orders of colours can be counted as the first trough passed by 550 nm. Higher order colours (after 3rd order) oscillate between weak pink-green colours and become increasingly white.




interference_filtered = data_intspec.filter(function(intspectra) {
  return biref == intspectra.biref;
})








